name: Flake Concept 1:26
description: The second in a series of minimal cellular automata expressing the principles of hexagonal consciousness. Here, an 8,000-cell cubic automaton cycles through a twelve-step loop under a simple single-neighbor rule. Each full-sized tetrahedron or octahedron indicates that the automaton state corresponding to the center of the cell or one of its vertices is active at that step.
